        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 7:08PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 708 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Robinson, or near
Crawfordville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Washington, Crawfordville, Union Point, Woodville, Rayle, Sharon,
Ficklin, Lundberg, Robinson, Daniel Springs, Newtown, Aonia, Celeste,
Rocky Creek Fire Dept., Lyneville, Raytown, Philomath, Alexander
Stephens Park, Sandy Cross, and Carters Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
